news.title: Thane: Yogeshwar Heights' compound wall collapses in Kalyan, FIR registered against builder
news.para: The CCTV footage of the building shows that the incident happened around 1:32am on Tuesday when the residents of Yogeshwar Building heard a loud sound of something falling.

news.title: Mohali: Consumer forum orders Palm Heights to refund buyer's money
news.para: Rajput, currently posted at 3BRD Chandigarh, had booked a 3BHK flat in Palm Heights project at Derabassi back in 2015. Like many homebuyers, she dreamed of a secure future in her own home.

news.title: Karnataka minister rejects EWS housing scheme graft charges, seeks probe
news.para: The minister was responding to claims made by ruling Congress MLA from Aland, B R Patil, who alleged that bribes were being collected from poor families in exchange for houses.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh government appoints new HP RERA chairperson & member
news.para: RD. Dhiman, IAS (Retd.), has been appointed as the Chairperson of Himachal Pradesh RERA, while Amit Kashyap, IAS (Retd.), has been named as a Member of HP RERA.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government eases building norms for small structures
news.para: Narayana, the municipal minister, said earlier, norms applied only to buildings above five floors, but now structures below five floors will also benefit from simplified approval.

news.title: Adani Group, Vedanta, others submit resolution plans to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Jaypee Infratech, which has been acquired by Mumbai-based Suraksha Group, has also submitted the bid, they added. Baba Ramdev-led Patanjali Ayurved, however, has not submitted the resolution plan after showing initial interest, sources said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh cabinet clears new land pooling rules for capital region
news.para: Parthasarathy noted that the land pooling rules have been framed with the vision of transforming Amaravati into a global city, a financial powerhouse for the state, attracting international educational institutions, establishing an airport, and fulfilling other development requirements.

news.title: Austrian prosecutors say they have wrapped up initial investigation into Signa
news.para: In a statement, they said there were four new strands, including an investigation into Signa founder Rene Benko and persons unknown on suspicion of favourable treatment to a creditor over a roughly 15 million euro ($17.4 million) repayment relating to a loan to Signa Prime at a time when that Signa unit was insolvent.

news.title: A $17 billion opportunity: Why global capital is chasing India’s office assets
news.para: India's commercial real estate sector has transformed into a globally competitive market, attracting multinational tenants and institutional investors. The office sector, driven by the growth of Global Capability Centers (GCCs) and REITs, offers high-quality spaces at competitive costs. This presents a compelling investment opportunity for global capital seeking stable, high-yielding assets in a rapidly expanding market.

news.title: Manasum Homes invests ₹150 crore to expand senior living footprint across South India
news.para: In Bengaluru, Manasum Homes has partnered with Tata Value Homes and developed RIVA. The project features 187 ready-to-move-in units.

news.title: TCS plans over ₹4,500 crore realty expansion across India
news.para: Tata Consultancy Services is investing over Rs 4,500 crore to expand its infrastructure across India, including new campuses and office spaces in key cities like Bengaluru, Kolkata, and Kochi. This expansion aligns with TCS's anticipated headcount growth and strong financial performance, signaling confidence in India's talent ecosystem and delivery capabilities.

news.title: Arbour invests ₹105 crore to ELV Projects’ residential developments in Bengaluru
news.para: As part of the transaction, Arbour Investments has already disbursed the first tranche of ₹20 crore.

news.title: Shivam Dube buys two apartments in Mumbai for ₹27.50 crore
news.para: The transaction was a primary purchase from Dev Land and Housing and includes three car parking spaces. It attracted a total stamp duty of ₹1.65 crore and registration charges of ₹30,000.

news.title: Kalpataru raises ₹708 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO launch
news.para: According to Kalpataru's regulatory filings, pre-sales and collections grew at a CAGR of 23% and 31%, respectively, between FY22 and FY24. Collections in the first nine months of FY25 stood at ₹2,621 crore, nearly equalling FY24’s total.

news.title: Aurum Alumni to invest ₹1,100 crore in two residential projects along Yamuna Expressway
news.para: A third project with an investment of 600 crore is also under planning and will be launched soon. Spread across three acres, Accord comprises five high-rise towers, each with 21 floors and will feature 210 4BHK units.

news.title: Hyderabad: Commercial plot in Gachibowli fetches ₹2.2 lakh per sq yard, goes for ₹33 crore
news.para: According to Telangana Housing Board (THB) commissioner VP Gautam, of the 11 plots auctioned, one commercial land parcel measuring 1,487 square yards in Gachibowli was sold at Rs 2.20 lakh per square yard, thereby fetching Rs 33 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue minister hints at major land law reform, amend plot size restrictions
news.para: "We are bringing a law that will permit one-guntha plot development in residential areas. Chief minister Devendra Fadnavis has already directed necessary amendments to the land fragmentation act, and we are initiating the next phase of reforms," said Revenue minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule.

news.title: National Housing Bank tightens refinancing rules to check 'misuse' of home loans
news.para: The National Housing Bank (NHB) has tightened norms for refinancing home loans, stipulating that refinance will only be provided for properties where less than half of the construction is complete at the time of the first disbursement.

news.title: Shortage of grade-A office space turns a stumbling block for Hi-Tec City in Hyderabad
news.para: HITEC City houses Sattva Group’s Knowledge Park and Knowledge City, RMZ’s Nexity, Raheja Mindspace, and CapitaLand Park, in addition to standalone projects by Auro Realty and My Home Group, among others.

news.title: Chandigarh administration finalises collector rate for Manimajra land pocket
news.para: This land is earmarked for a multi-storey residential society, and the municipal corporation (MC) is now actively preparing the terms and conditions for its disposal via e-auction.
